{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-projects-post-template-js","path":"/projects/20210313 - Anand Bhai/basic/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<hr>\n<p><img src=\"/37ef91e2b108415a3b7ec9d8eb591c55/anand.gif\" alt=\"Blink\"> </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Souruly/Processing-Projects/tree/main/Anand%20Bhai/Anand_Bhai\" target=\"_blank\">Link to Project Repo</a></p>\n<p>I wanted to make a kind of installation that we can have in a corridor, inspired from Anand Bhai's character in <a href=\"https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0374887/\" target=\"_blank\">Link to Project Repo</a></p>\n<p>As some background, Anand Bhai is a patient(case study) in a medical college/hospital. He has been unresponsive for the last however many decades.</p>\n<p>Now when the protagonist comes along, we notice that Anand Bhai only responds(blinks) to his presence, and that too only when nobody else is watching.</p>\n<p>So in this project I used OpenCV Face Detection to detect whether a face is visible and only when no face is visible, initiate the blinking sequence.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 548px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/be38f545e2f37cadf96f462f7d50b782/a58fe/face_vis.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 104.05405405405406%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Face Visible\"\n        title=\"Face Visible\"\n        src=\"/static/be38f545e2f37cadf96f462f7d50b782/a58fe/face_vis.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/be38f545e2f37cadf96f462f7d50b782/12f09/face_vis.png 148w,\n/static/be38f545e2f37cadf96f462f7d50b782/e4a3f/face_vis.png 295w,\n/static/be38f545e2f37cadf96f462f7d50b782/a58fe/face_vis.png 548w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 548px) 100vw, 548px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nThe small green dot on the bottom right corner tells that a face is visible</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 547px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ad7caf0757d2bf3facfd8902203d6204/977f7/face_notvis2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 104.05405405405406%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Face Not Visible\"\n        title=\"Face Not Visible\"\n        src=\"/static/ad7caf0757d2bf3facfd8902203d6204/977f7/face_notvis2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ad7caf0757d2bf3facfd8902203d6204/12f09/face_notvis2.png 148w,\n/static/ad7caf0757d2bf3facfd8902203d6204/e4a3f/face_notvis2.png 295w,\n/static/ad7caf0757d2bf3facfd8902203d6204/977f7/face_notvis2.png 547w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 547px) 100vw, 547px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\nThe small dot is red, that means no face is visible. So Anand Bhai is free to blink and communicate.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><u><strong>PS(13th March 2021)</strong></u> : <br>\nThis project is about 3 years old now. I was just learning about reading files, images in Java, OpenCV, Face Detection and this tied everything together. Back in the college days when everything was about memes and joking around, I had a lot of fun making this and showing it to my friends.</p>\n<p>It may have some problems, but the github link is available. You can download the code and make changes if you want.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Anand Bhai","author":"Sourav Kulkarni","date":"31 May, 2018"},"excerpt":"Blink  Link to Project Repo I wanted to make a kind of installation that we can have in a corridor, inspired from Anand Bhai's character inâ€¦","timeToRead":1}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/20210313 - Anand Bhai/basic/","templatePath":"./src/templates/projects-post-template.js"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}